cs.CL, cs.SD, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SI 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with speech repairs and edit terms on transcripts. It could also belong to cs.SD (Sound) as it deals with speech processing. Additionally, it uses information-theoretic measures from n-gram models, which could fall under cs.LG (Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the system proposed in the paper uses classifiers to detect different stages of repairs, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
